1927 her nephew king michael was forced to abdicate by the 
communists in 1947 and lives in switzerland 
i didnt expect the whole thing i must say ive lived with 
it so long its been 42 years since i left she said 
the strength of the country has always been in its peasantry 
thats what ceausescu was destroying i hope there is enough of 
them left and enough intellectuals left to be able to build again 
princess ileana was exiled from romania with the rest of the 
royal family soon after king michaels abdication in december 1947 
she immigrated with her husband an archduke of austria and 
their six children to switzerland and then argentina before 
settling in 1950 in the united states the move ultimately led to 
divorce 
she ended a second marriage to become a postulant or a 
candidate for the religious order in 1961 six years later she 
took her monastic vows and put up a trailer outside ellwood city to 
began building an englishspeaking monastery for orthodox women of 
all ethnic backgrounds 
mother alexandra said she has spent much of the past week on the 
telephone with friends and relatives in europe keeping abreast of 
developments and consoling friends of the many who died in the 
uprising 
she said that even with the changes elsewhere in eastern europe 
she did not expect such quick drastic moves in her homeland 
quite honestly i was feeling very depressed about it she 
said i thought everybody was doing something but nothing was 
moving in romania at all and suddenly it blew up 
mother alexandra said she is working with the romanian orthodox 
episcopate of america in jackson mich to organize a save romania 
fund she also plans a special service at the monastery this week 
for romanias dead 
she said she would consider returning to romania if i could be 
of use 
</TEXT>
