<TEXT>
a strikebound coal company sued the 
united mine workers for 60 million wednesday accusing the union 
and its members of attempted murder arson and extortion as part of 
a nationwide racketeering scheme 
the lawsuit was filed in federal court in beckley by the new 
beckley mining corp which also announced it will close its nearby 
glen daniel mine because of what it called union violence stemming 
from the umws selective strikes 
the umw has been on strike against new beckley since january 
idling 130 miners the union also is engaged in a bitter strike 
against the pittston coal group inc in west virginia virginia and 
kentucky 
the lawsuit was filed under the racketeer influenced corrupt 
organizations act although the racketeering statute was intended 
by congress primarily as a tool against organized crime it been 
used frequently against unions including a 1988 lawsuit by the 
government against the the teamsters 
earlier this year the supreme court upheld the use of the 
statute against legitimate organizations despite complaints by the 
aflcio that it had become a tool of harassment against 
legitimate businesses and labor organizations 
the new beckley mining lawsuit cites alleged violence at more 
than 20 coal companies in west virginia kentucky and virginia 
since 1983 when the union began its selective strike strategy in 
which the umw targeted specific companies for work stoppages 
previous strikes were industrywide 
the lawsuit alleges that new beckley employees have been the 
targets of vandalism death threats shootings and beatings at work 
and at home 
the violence pervades the coal industry discouraging 
productivity and inhibiting the economic wellbeing of individuals 
living and working in coalproducing communities the lawsuit 
says 
union spokesman john duray called the lawsuit ridiculous and 
accused the company of engaging in a pressrelease lawsuit by 
hiring a public relations company to notify the news media of the 
filing 
it looks to me like these guys are a lot more interested in 
trying their case in the media than in court duray said 
district 29 president everett acord said he knew nothing of the 
lawsuit or the mine closing 
at a news conference on the courthouse steps new beckley 
president jay sasell said the decision to shut down and seal new 
beckleys glen daniel mine was reached because the continued 
organized violence orchestrated against new beckley by the umwa has 
reached an intolerable level of acceptability by any rational 
standard 
marauding pickets continue to cause great hardship upon the 
company and its families on a daily basis 
the lawsuit contends that the union has engaged in a pattern of 
racketeering that includes 34 counts of attempted murder 23 of 
arson and 79 of extortion 
under the rico statute the companys requested 20 million in 
damages can be tripled if the union and various individuals are 
found to have violated the act 
</TEXT>
