<TEXT>
snow fell wednesday from the mississippi valley to the 
appalachians and temperatures hit record lows in the northeast 
at midday snow fell over minnesota wisconsin michigan 
eastern indiana eastern kentucky ohio west virginia western 
pennsylvania western new york state and western virginia 
freezing rain was mixed with the snow over central indiana 
southwestern lower michigan and northcentral ohio 
snow also was reported in northwestern north carolina 
the heaviest snowfall during the six hours up to noon was 3 
inches at muskegon mich 
record lows were 6 below zero at binghamton ny 13 below at 
elkins wva and 11 below at syracuse ny huntington wva 
tied its record of 4 and philadelphia tied its record of 8 
wednesdays low for the lower 48 states was 37 degrees below 
zero at watertown ny 
the national weather service said this has been the coldest 
december in new york state since 1831 it said the average 
temperature in albany for the first 26 days of december was 131 
degrees compared to the record of 172 degrees set in 1831 in 
buffalo the temperature averaged 165 degrees through the day 
after christmas 3 degrees lower than the previous record set in 
1876 
temperatures around the nation at 3 pm est ranged from zero at 
massena ny to 75 at beeville texas 
